
Two Conyers residents and a Lithonia woman will represent Georgia at the 2005 White House Conference on Aging. Martha Eaves, of Conyers, was appointed as a delegate to the conference by Gov. Sonny Perdue. Sen. Johnny Isakson appointed Steven Weiniger of Conyers. Rep. Cynthia McKinney appointed Carleen Cumberbatch of Lithonia. The conference will be held in Washington Dec. 11-14. Delegates are to discuss policies on aging for the next 10 years and beyond. 

